The paper deals with high-resolution video frame prediction, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach using a convolutional module, which involves learning motion vectors and kernels for each pixel. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper mentions that their approach can handle large motion effectively, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
